NOTE ON MODEL WEIGHTS

This repository contains source code only. It bundles, hosts, and redistributes
NO machine-learning model weights of any kind — there are no .onnx (or .data)
files tracked in git, and none are shipped in any release built from this source
as published. All models are supplied by the end user at runtime, downloaded to
the user's own machine. As a result, no model license attaches to this
MIT-licensed source distribution.

The decisions below only become relevant if you build a packaged artifact
(installer / MSIX / release asset) that embeds a weights file, or otherwise
redistribute weights yourself:

- YOLO26 weights are licensed AGPL-3.0 by Ultralytics. The app fetches them only
  onto the user's machine via scripts/download-models.ps1 (or the user exports
  them from the Ultralytics .pt files). They are NEVER part of this repository or
  its source distribution. Anyone who downloads, uses, or redistributes those
  weights is subject to Ultralytics' AGPL-3.0 terms and may need an Ultralytics
  Enterprise License for closed-source commercial distribution:
  https://www.ultralytics.com/license
  Do NOT embed AGPL weights in a packaged build you intend to ship under MIT.
- If you want to ship a build with a model included, choose a permissively
  licensed model (e.g. an Apache-2.0 or MIT one) and include its license/NOTICE
  in that artifact.
- COCO class labels derive from the COCO 2017 dataset (Common Objects in
  Context); the dataset annotations are licensed CC BY 4.0.

